    "Several standard ML algorithms are commonly used for sentiment analysis in health-related research.",
    "These include Naïve Bayes (NB), Support Vector Machines (SVM), Logistic Regression (LR), Random Forests (RF), and others (24) (25) (26).",
    "SVMs, in particular, have often been a popular choice in health sentiment",
    "Comparison of sentiment analysis methodologies for public health data.",
    "Methodology Principle Strengths Weaknesses Public health use cases Example tools and algorithms Lexicon-based Uses predefined dictionaries (lexicons) with word sentiment scores to calculate overall text sentiment."
